.\" Manpage for simple_shell.
.TH simple_shell 1 "2023-15-05" GNU "simple_shell user manual"

.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- A mini version UNIX shell (A command line interpreter)

.SH SYNOPSIS
Run the executable created after compiling. For example gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o simple_shell
.br
.B ./simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
Creates a prompt where a user can enter valid commands to be executed. You have the option to provide a valid path to the executable of a command of interest.
.br
Advanced features such as variable expansions, pattern matching, redirection, piping, among others that the original shell provides are not implemented.

.SH USAGE
The following are some of the common commands that can be run

.br
.B /bin/ls
- Lists files in current working directory (Note that the path to binary to provided)

.br
.B ls [[option]...[file] ... ]
- Lists files in current working directory

.br
.B exit [status_code]
- Exits out of the shell and returns to original shell

.br
.B pwd
- Prints the working directory

.br
.B More
- You can execute many other commands like df

.SH EXAMPLE
Type 
.B ./simple_shell 
in your terminal to invoke

.sp
.br
.B "#cisfun$ "
- An empty prompt is shown
.br 
.B "#cisfun$ ls -l" 
- prints all files in current directory

.SH RETURN VALUES
Result of executed command e.g files for ls or nothing e.g when exit is executed

.SH BUGS
No known bugs

